[3] Somalia
Date: 27 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Polio Eradication website [edited]
<http://www.polioeradication.org/casecount.asp#details>

According to the polio eradication website, as of 19 Dec 2006 there
have been 32 cases of polio confirmed in Somalia during 2006, as
compared with 101 cases confirmed in the same period in 2005. The
website also had the following "pre-notification" (not officially
reported to WHO as yet) information:
"Pre-notification of a case (type 1) was received from Togdher
province. The case had onset of paralysis on 8 Nov [2006]. Two NIDs
have been held since this latest case, in early November [2006] and
on 10 Dec [2006]. Somalia's next SNIDs will be held in early January [2007]."
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The above information on the polio activity in Somalia is not
surprising, given the reports of 2 recent cases of polio in Kenya
among residents of a Somalian refugee camp in Garissa, Kenya. ProMED
reported on the cases in the camp in prior postings (see
Poliomyelitis - Worldwide (15) & (19): Kenya ex Somalia -- see
below). As a reminder, genotyping of some of the earlier isolates
from Somalia and the isolate from the 1st confirmed case in a
Somalian refugee camp in Kenya revealed the origin of these viruses
to be Nigeria, where polio is still endemic.
Good maps of Somalia can be found at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/somalia_pol02.jpg> and
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/somalia.pdf>.
- Mod.MPP]
